  "text": "In a study of 10 wheat and 18 triticale lines it was confirmed that wheat was hardier than triticale in terms of field survival [CITATION_1] . Few studies which sought suitable cold tolerance phenotyping methods with triticale concluded that appreciable variation exists in triticale for this trait (e.g. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . It is therefore clear that cold hardy triticale must be produced with cold hardy wheat parents and that the rye genome component per se is no assurance for triticale cold tolerance.",
